                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-49-off279 t18181028-49-crimeloc282"></join>. On the 16th of September, about half-past five o'clock in the evening, I saw somebody leave the shop, and missed the looking-glass off a chest of drawers - I ran out, and found the prisoner with it under his arm, in Chapel-street. He said it was his own.</p>
